question:
What is the result of the following right shift operation?

```cpp
int x = 8;
x = x >> 2;
cout << x << endl;
```

What will the following code output?

```cpp
int y = 16;
y = y >> 3;
cout << y << endl;
```

What is the result of the following right shift operation?

```cpp
int z = 32;
z = z >> 4;
cout << z << endl;
```

What is the value of 'x' after this operation?

```cpp
int x = 64;
x = x >> 2;
cout << x << endl;
```

What happens when you right shift a negative number?

```cpp
int a = -8;
a = a >> 2;
cout << a << endl;
```

What is the result of the following right shift operation?

```cpp
int b = 1;
b = b >> 1;
cout << b << endl;
```

How do you shift a number by 1 position to the right in C++?

```cpp
int c = 16;
c = c >> 1;
cout << c << endl;
```

Which of the following is true for the right shift operator in C++?

```cpp
int x = 4;
x = x >> 1;
cout << x << endl;
```
